    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This *+1 resilient full plate* is crafted from the most colorful fragments chipped from scales of a dragon turtle's shell, traditionally incorporating that motif in the form of a thicker, sturdier backplate. While wearing this armor, you aren't flat-footed from creatures that flank you, and you ignore the armor's speed penalty when you Swim and its check penalty to Athletics checks to Swim.",
        "level": 12,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Abjuration",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 628",
                            "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 628",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        },
                        "page": 628,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "4.0",
                            "alt": "4.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "fd5735184d8cc7e06debda7ae557fa0d",
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the abjuration school of magic, typically involving protection or wards.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Invested",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 98,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 219,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
                "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "invest",
                        "alt": "invest",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2799
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
